SIMPLE: frozen
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frozen
<hw>Fro"zen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Congealed
with cold; affected by freezing; <as>as, a <ex>frozen</ex>
brook</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They warmed their <qex>frozen</qex> feet.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Subject to frost, or to long and severe cold;
chilly; <as>as, the <ex>frozen</ex> north; the <ex>frozen</ex>
zones.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Cold-hearted; unsympathetic; unyielding.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be not ever <qex>frozen</qex>, coy.</q> <rj><qau>T.
Carew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frozenness</ent>⟦br⟧
